CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, February 22, 1958, pg. 3, reads: "Not Going to Sell - Earl J. Huff of 7761 Baxter St., Brushton, tacks a 'This House Not for Sale' sign on his home, as a first step in easing intergroup tensions in Homewood - Brushton area. The Rev. J. Davis Barkley, minister of the Brushton Methodist Church, requested help from the City's Commission on Human Relations, and the plan is designed to thwart greedy and cunning real estate brokers. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Earl J. Huff nailing sign reading "This House Not for Sale" to porch railing of his home, 7761 Baxter Street, Homewood
